      <title>The Elephant and the Dragon</title>
      <chapter>
        <paragraph>China’s socialist market economy is the world's second largest economy by nominal GDP and the world’s fastest-growing major economy, with growth rates averaging 10% over 30 years. China is a global hub for manufacturing, it's the largest exporter of goods in the world and the world’s fastest growing consumer market.</paragraph>
        <paragraph>As of 2015 there was talk of a “slowing” Chinese economy, referred to a slowing of the rate of economic growth and of indstrial sector like manufactory.</paragraph>
      </chapter>
